  <p>Dynamic text functions in the same way as <strong>dynamic content</strong>. Refer to the <a href="../../designing/using/defining-dynamic-content-in-an-email.md">Definig dynamic content</a> section.</p> 
  <note>
   <p> For SMS and push, you can only define dynamic text. Defining dynamic text is specific to the <a href="../../designing/using/about-email-content-design.md#using-the-email-content-editor">content editor</a>. If you want to define dynamic text with the <a href="../../designing/using/about-email-content-design.md#using-the-creative-designer">Creative Designer</a>, see <a href="../../designing/using/defining-dynamic-content-in-an-email.md" target="_blank">Defining dynamic content in an email</a>. </p> 
  </note>
  <p>You can define dynamic text:</p> 
  <ul>
   <li><p>in an email subject</p> </li>
   <li><p>in HTML mode</p> </li>
   <li><p>in text mode</p> </li>
  </ul>
  <p>To define dynamic text:</p> 
  <ol>
   <li><p>Select text in the body of your message.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/delivery_content_39.png" title="" /></li>
   <li><p>Click <strong>Enable dynamic text</strong>.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/delivery_content_40.png" title="" /><p>The <strong>Dynamic text</strong> option then appears in the palette.</p> <p>It is configured in the same way as dynamic content.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/delivery_content_41.png" title="" /><p>A purple frame appears around dynamic text in the body of the email.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/delivery_content_42.png" title="" /></li>
  </ol>
